New Records: Alperen Sengun put up 25 points and 14 rebounds on 11-of-15 shooting
Fred VanVleet had a bounceback game with 19 points, five assists, two steals, and one block on 8-of-14 shooting
Key Match Events: The Rockets outscored the Knicks 20-19 in the third quarter, and then 28-22 in the fourth
The Rockets guarded Knicks superstar Jalen Brunson, limiting him to 29 points on 9-of-24 shooting
Post-Match Reflections: The Rockets' stars showing out in the win is a great sign
The team relied on depth when VanVleet and Sengun were underperforming, but they played great basketball and backed it up on both ends
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets will try to make this a winning streak as they face the San Antonio Spurs for the third time tomorrow
Others: Jed Katz, a student at the University of Wisconsin-Madison, contributed to the article
